/Adele@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/adele">阿黛尔</a>向歌迷透露了她新发现的清醒状态，并承认自己在 20 多岁的时候是一个“边缘酒鬼”。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/adele-30-album-review-dependable-pop-titan-finally-mixes-things-up-3096613">阿黛尔 – “30”专辑评论：可靠的流行巨星终于把事情搞混了</a></strong></li></ul><p>这位流行偶像在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-adele-begin-long-awaited-las-vegas-residency-setlist-video-photos-3352060">拉斯维加斯驻场</a>期间宣布了这一消息，她告诉歌迷她最近戒了酒，这样她就可以陪伴她 10 岁的儿子安杰洛 (Angelo)。</p><p> “我大概在三个半月前就停止喝酒了，”她（通过<a href="https://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-12644157/I-borderline-alcoholic-quite-lot-20s-Adele-reveals-gave-drinking-three-months-ago-says-boring-miss-much.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《每日邮报</em></a>》）说道。 “这很无聊。我的意思是，在我 20 多岁的大部分时间里，我确实处于酗酒的边缘，但我非常怀念它。我也戒掉了咖啡因。”</p><p>她还直接与一位在演出中享用饮品的粉丝交谈，并补充道：“所以享受你的酸威士忌吧。我非常非常嫉妒。”</p><p>这并不是阿黛尔第一次公开她过去与酒精的关系。此前，这位《Chasing Pavements》歌手表示，她的饮酒习惯在大流行期间恶化，并表示在 2020 年新冠封锁期间，她曾在午餐前喝了四瓶葡萄酒。</p><p> “我记得当我在新冠肺炎疫情封锁期间来到这里时，那是上午 11 点，我就像喝了四瓶酒一样——就像我们所有人一样，”她（通过<a href="https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/1825195/adele-borderline-alcoholic-gave-up-drinking-health-news" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Express</em></a> ）说道。 “我在 2020 年就说过我想推出我的专辑。我们基本上都在家里喝醉了。”</p><p>在周六（10 月 14 日）的现场表演中，这位歌手还透露，她正在计划为明天（10 月 19 日）就满 11 岁的儿子举办庆祝活动。 </p><figure id="attachment_3517248" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3517248" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3517248" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270.jpg" alt="Adele poses with the Best Pop Solo Performance Award for &quot;Easy on Me&quot; in the press room during the 65th GRAMMY Awards at Crypto.com Arena on February 05, 2023" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Adele-Grammy@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3517248" class="wp-caption-text"> Adele poses with the Best Pop Solo Performance Award for “Easy on Me” in the press room during the 65th GRAMMY Awards at Crypto.com Arena on February 05, 2023. CREDIT: Alberto E. Rodriguez/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> “He is very much like me because I take my birthday very seriously,” she explained. “So it is a whole week or a month celebration which I think everyone should treat their birthday like.”</p><p> The announcement about her sobriety is just one of the interesting moments to unravel at the singer&#39;s <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/watch-adele-begin-long-awaited-las-vegas-residency-setlist-video-photos-3352060">Weekends With Adele&#39; residency</a> .</p><p> This comes as the show previously made headlines when <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/adele-responds-to-fan-proposal-you-cant-marry-me-im-straight-my-love-3501073">a fan proposed to her</a> and when she said she <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/adele-says-shes-no-longer-taking-selfies-during-her-las-vegas-shows-3498880">would no longer be taking selfies with</a> concertgoers due to worries that she may catch COVID-19.</p><p> Additionally, last month, she <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/adele-explains-how-security-had-to-remove-fucking-raucous-recent-audience-members-3503682">explained how her security team had to remove some “fucking raucous” audience members</a> at the shows.</p><p> “Last weekend&#39;s shows were fucking raucous, it was Mexican Independence,” she began. “There were lots of celebrations going on outside and when there is a party atmosphere, it makes everyone want to party.”</p><p> “So many people had to leave the show because they were acting so wild. They were being disruptive and stuff. It was absolutely crazy,” she added. “There was one lady at the front whose boob kept falling out. She must&#39;ve been sunbathing until late because she came in basically in a bikini and a cover.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/adele-admits-she-was-borderline-alcoholic-in-her-20s-but-is-now-sober-3517241">Adele admits she was “borderline alcoholic” in her 20s, but is now sober</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
